                          <item xml:id="e3">
                            <locus from="123r" to="123v" facs="125">Fols 123r–123v</locus>
                            <desc>Scrawls</desc>
                          </item>
                          <item xml:id="e4">
                            <desc>
                              Scribal intervention: words of text are written interlinearly <locus target="#58v #93r" facs="061 095">folss. 58v, 93r, </locus>;
                              and lines of text are written interlinearly <locus target="#2v" facs="005">2v, </locus>;
                              erasure markings are visible <locus target="#11v" facs="014"> f. 11v, line 9</locus>; <locus target="#44r" facs="046"> f. 44r, lines 3 and 6</locus>; <locus target="#47v" facs="050"> f. 47v,
                              line 19 to correct repeated word</locus>; <locus target="#64v" facs="067"> f. 64v, line 6</locus>; <locus target="#90v" facs="093"> f. 90v, line 15 to correct repeated words</locus>; <locus target="#96r" facs="099"> f. 96r, line 16</locus>; etc.
                            </desc>
                          </item>
                          <item xml:id="e5">
                            <desc>
                             <locus target="#11v" facs="014">Fol. 11v</locus>, line 16: word has lines drawn above and below it to signal its erasure in order to correct homoeoteleuton.
                              </desc>
                          </item>
                          <item xml:id="e6">
                            <desc>
                              The scribe’s chosen aspect ratio for the codex combined with the script size forces the scribe to complete the line of text above or below the end of the line (throughout). But, where the line of text is still too long, the scribe reduces the font size at the end of lines to avoid having to go onto the next line throughout the codex (e.g. <locus target="#1r #2r #5v #10v" facs="003 004 008 013">Fols. 1r, 2r, 5v, 10v</locus>).
                            </desc>
                          </item>
                              </list>
                          </additions>
